    whoYouAre: [
      `You are not a covenant keeper who happens to teach. You are teaching in your grace — and what you are sent to keep is covenant with the truth itself. You do not bend doctrine for popularity. You do not soften teaching for comfort. You hold a covenant with what is true — even when that costs you platforms, audiences, or relationships. Your loyalty is not to a tradition. It is to the integrity of what you have been given to teach.`,
      `This combination is rare and necessary. Most teachers eventually negotiate with their teaching to keep their audience. You don't.`,
    ],
    assignment: `You are called to be the keeper of true teaching across seasons of cultural pressure. Your assignment is to remain faithful to what is right — even when what is right becomes unpopular, inconvenient, or controversial. You are sent to be the voice that is still teaching the same truth in 20 years that you are teaching today, because the truth itself has not changed and your covenant with it has not weakened.`,
    strength: `You can teach the same truth through changing seasons without compromising it. Where others adjust to the moment, you teach the moment back to the truth. This is why people return to your teaching across decades. It does not feel dated. It feels durable.`,
